1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,330
A young bank executive related this personal experience about work capacity.

2
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:10,449
One of the other executives in our bank left us with very short notice.

3
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:12,850
This put our department on the spot.

4
00:00:12,959 --> 00:00:19,410
The fellow leaving had filled an important job, and his work couldn't be postponed or left undone.

5
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:25,090
The day after he left, the vice president in charge of my department called me in.

6
00:00:25,199 --> 00:00:30,529
He explained to me that he had already talked individually to the two others in my group,

7
00:00:30,719 --> 00:00:36,930
asking them if they could divide the work of the man who had just left until a replacement could be found.

8
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:45,410
Neither of them flatly refused, said the vice president, but each stated that he is up to his neck now with his own pressing work.

9
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:49,890
I'm wondering if you could handle some of the overload temporarily?

10
00:00:50,479 --> 00:00:56,930
Throughout my working career, I've learned that it never pays to turn down what looks like an opportunity.

11
00:00:57,120 --> 00:01:04,930
So I agreed and promised to do my very best to handle all the vacated job as well as keep up with my own work.

12
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:07,570
The Vice President was pleased at this.

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,050
I walked out of his office knowing I had taken on a big job.

14
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:17,890
I was just as busy as the two others in my department who had wiggled out of this extra duty.

15
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,650
But I was determined to find a way to handle both jobs.

16
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:25,969
I finished up my work that afternoon, and when the offices were closed,

17
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:30,610
I sat down to figure out how I could increase my personal efficiency.

18
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:35,410
I got a pencil and started writing down every idea I could think of.

19
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:46,769
And you know, I came up with some good ones, like working out an arrangement with my secretary to channel all routine telephone calls to me during a certain hour each day,

20
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:54,290
placing all outgoing calls during a certain hour, cutting my usual conference periods from fifteen minutes to ten,

21
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,570
giving all my dictation at one time each day.

22
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:06,290
I also discovered my secretary could and was eager to take over a number of little time-consuming details for me.

23
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:11,410
I had been handling my present job for over two years, and frankly,

24
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:16,209
I was amazed to discover how much inefficiency I had let creep in.

25
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:23,009
Within a week's time, I was dictating twice as many letters, handling fifty percent more phone calls,

26
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:27,330
attending half again as many meetings, all with no strain.

27
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,650
A couple more weeks passed.

28
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,969
The vice president called me in.

29
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,690
He complimented me on doing a fine job.

30
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:40,690
He went on to say that he had looked over a number of people from both inside and outside the bank,

31
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:43,170
but he had not yet found the right man.

32
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:48,370
Then he confessed that he had already cleared with the bank's executive committee,

33
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:53,489
and they had authorized him to combine the two jobs, put them both in my charge,

34
00:02:53,489 --> 00:02:56,610
and give me a substantial increase in salary.

35
00:02:57,280 --> 00:03:03,170
I prove to myself that how much I can do depends on how much I think I can do.

36
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:07,489
Capacity is indeed a state of mind.

